OL,3,CMan who served 36 years in jail for
OL,4,Cmurder launches new bid to clear his
OL,5,Cname
OL,7,F"You can't let one out and then say
OL,8,Fthe evidence is ok, when the appeal
OL,9,Fcourt's already ruled the evidence is
OL,10,Fuseless."
OL,12,FRay is now waiting to hear if his
OL,13,Flatest attempt to get the CCRC to look
OL,14,Finto his case will be successful -
OL,15,Fseveral other bids have been
OL,16,Funsuccessful.
OL,18,FBut he now has the support of
OL,19,Findependent investigator Stephanie
OL,20,FDavies.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
