OL,5,Cname
OL,7,F"Ray was vulnerable when he was
OL,8,Fquestioned," she said.
OL,10,F"I think the police may have been
OL,11,Faware that he was vulnerable and he's
OL,12,Fended up confessing to a crime that I
OL,13,Fdon't think he did.
OL,15,F"The details in his confessions don't
OL,16,Fmatch what I'm seeing at the crime
OL,17,Fscene."
OL,19,FShe added: "Every time Ray's applied
OL,20,Fto the CCRC, they have said there's no
OL,21,Fnew evidence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
